OL,3,CPeston: Why wasn't Kaddour-Cherif
OL,4,Cdeported?
OL,6,FIn essence, he was protected because
OL,7,Fthere were outstanding criminal
OL,8,Fproceedings against him.
OL,10,FThe government does not remove or
OL,11,Fdeport people while criminal
OL,12,Fproceedings are ongoing, unless there
OL,13,Fis agreement with the police and Crown
OL,14,FProsecution Service.
OL,16,F> Why are foreign criminals being paid
OL,17,Fto leave the UK?
