OL,3,CPeston: Why wasn't Kaddour-Cherif
OL,4,Cdeported?
OL,6,FHe had, for example, been convicted in
OL,7,FNovember 2024 of indecent exposure,
OL,8,Fand was sentenced to an 18-month
OL,9,Fcommunity order. He was also placed on
OL,10,Fthe sex offenders register.
OL,12,FBut - and here is what some will see
OL,13,Fas extraordinary - the deportation
OL,14,Fproceedings were not progressed
OL,15,Fbecause of pending prosecutions.
OL,17,FThe unfortunate consequence is that he
OL,18,Fwas released mistakenly from custody,
OL,19,Fhaving been remanded for trespass with
OL,20,Fintent to steal, and has now vanished.
